Fenerbahce Signs Everton Defender Yobo, Striker Bienvenu From Young Boys

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-09-06T07:41:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/fenerbahce-signs-everton-defender-yobo-striker-bienvenu-from-young-boys.html
Turkey’s Fenerbahce soccer club
signed Everton defender Joseph Yobo and  Switzerland ’s  Young Boys 
striker Henri Bienvenu for the following season, according to
two statements to the stock exchange by the team’s listed
merchandising arm.  Yobo, originally from Nigeria, will received a guaranteed
salary of 2.35 million euros ($3.3 million) for the 2011-2012
season while Everton will receive a 700,000 euro transfer fee,
Fenerbahce said.  Bienvenu, from Cameroon, signed a four-year contract for a
guaranteed salary of 4 million euros, with Young Boys in
Switzerland receiving another 4 million euros in fees,
Fenerbahce said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
